../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:7:The chain is at its best when it refuses cosmetic exact-rewrite optimism. It is weakest where it assumes that "destroyed by Tao averaging" can be operationalized into a usable screening rule without importing substantial additional technical structure.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- "State exactly what Tao's averaged equations preserve" is not yet a concrete task unless the chain names the comparison granularity. Preserve at what level: identities, coercive estimates, local energy inequalities, geometric transport, concentration scenarios, or blowup mechanisms? Without that, the preserved/destroyed ledger will be partly semantic.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:26:- The example list already nudges the search toward currently fashionable exact-NS markers: pressure Hessian, alignment, circulation/topology, stochastic flow. That is not neutral curation; it preloads the outcome with mechanisms already easy to narrate in Tao-filter language.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:28:- "One-line Tao verdicts" and "one-line novelty notes" are too compressed for the burden being placed on them. A one-line verdict is exactly how a subtle but ambiguous candidate gets prematurely labeled "identity-level" and buried.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:68:### 1. The chain confuses Tao-discrimination with proof relevance
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:70:The mission filter is necessary, but this chain treats it as almost sufficient for early-stage ranking. That is not warranted. Many features are genuinely absent from the averaged model and still mathematically useless for regularity. The chain knows this in words, but its workflow still gives Tao-discrimination too much agenda-setting power.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:94:- It correctly treats Tao's averaged-model obstruction as a hard filter rather than background color.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-01.md:101:If this chain is kept, it should be interpreted primarily as a falsification chain, not a discovery-ranking chain. The honest success condition is not "produce 1-2 promoted discriminators." It is "show, under a strict admissibility and comparability standard, whether any candidate survives contact with a named bottleneck in a way that is stronger than slogan-level Tao discrimination." Without that tightening, the most likely output is a polished ranking memo with weak epistemic content.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:10:- The example families already bias the search toward three particular lenses: graph closure, leakage ratio, and delayed-threshold behavior. Those are not neutral. `interaction-graph closure` is likely too combinatorial and basis-sensitive; `leakage-ratio closure` quietly presupposes a norm, normalization, and threshold choice; `delayed-threshold behavioral closure` risks hard-coding Tao's averaged mechanism back into the object.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:12:- The chain never says which features of Tao's circuit are essential and which are dispensable. Without that, Step 1 can manufacture formulas that look precise while tracking the wrong phenomenon.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:36:- A delayed-threshold mechanism is specifically time-sensitive. If the chain refuses any definition that needs a nontrivial finite time horizon or a parameter family, it may rule out the most Tao-relevant formulations by design.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md:59:- The final kill condition only flags one kind of circularity: hard-coding Tao's averaged construction back into exact NS language. But circularity can also enter through tuned thresholds, cherry-picked time windows, or choosing a packet representation that predetermines leakage.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The problem is that the chain is still mostly a Kenig-Merle style template with the key novelty compressed into an undefined phrase: "an exact NS structure unavailable to Tao's averaged model." Until that phrase is made concrete, the chain is not a research program so much as a hope that one missing NS-only rigidity input exists. The biggest risk is not that the chain is too ambitious; it is that it can generate polished memos while never confronting the actual hard obstruction.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:26:- The filter "reject anything Tao's averaged model plausibly preserves" is not a reliable research criterion. A lever can fail in the averaged model for irrelevant reasons, or survive averaging and still be exactly the right tool for real NS.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- Requiring Tao-sensitivity before the extraction package is built biases the search toward novelty theater. It rewards mechanisms that sound NS-specific rather than mechanisms that can actually be applied to an almost-periodic critical element.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:31:The kill condition is too aggressive in one direction and too permissive in another. It is too aggressive because a promising route might only reveal the right rigidity quantity after the minimal object is formulated. It is too permissive because merely "naming" a Tao-sensitive lever is not progress unless one can state its sign, monotonicity, coercivity, or contradiction mechanism on the intended class of solutions.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:55:The downgrade rule is also too binary. A lever can fail without collapsing to Tao-preserved structure. It can fail because the compactness class is too weak, because the quantity is not coercive, or because the limiting object lacks the regularity needed to state the argument. Those are different failure modes and should be separated.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:71:- The Tao-averaged-model filter is doing too much conceptual work. "Unavailable to Tao's averaged model" is not itself evidence of relevance, tractability, or sharpness.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:33:- The ledger language encourages overcounting. A mode can be kinematically forced yet dynamically negligible, cancelled, or damped on the time scale that matters for Tao-like behavior.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- "Finite-packet non-closure" is not automatically a stronger obstruction. It only kills one model class. The mission target is near-closed Tao-like behavior, not necessarily strict finite packet closure.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:45:- A closure ledger is only kinematic data. A lower bound requires showing that the forced channels contribute in a norm and on a time scale that actually competes with the desired Tao-like channels.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:48:- Reducing the problem to a finite optimization over geometry parameters may throw away the most important difficulty: delayed-threshold dynamics. Tao's mechanism is not just one-step interaction magnitude.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:54:### Step 4 - Stress-test the bound against adversarial geometry and helicity choices
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:58:- Geometry and helicity are not post hoc perturbations. They determine the ledger itself. If they are only stress-tested after a lower-bound worksheet is built, the chain risks deriving a bound for the wrong object.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:61:- Conversely, a weaker-norm positive bound may be too weak to matter. The chain names that possibility but does not say how to judge whether such a bound still bears on the Tao-circuit question.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:73:- An explicit low-leakage family is not yet a serious anti-obstruction result unless it also preserves the Tao-like role logic over a meaningful time window. Instantaneous low leakage is weaker than near-circuit dynamics.
