../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-03.md:68:### Step 5 - Close with a Tao-sensitive verdict
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-03.md:73:- "Same argument works unchanged in the averaged model" is too binary. A mechanism can fail to be fully Tao-sensitive and still rely on mild exact structure. The real question is whether that structure yields decisive control, not merely formal distinction.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-03.md:136:The fair verdict is that this chain should be run mainly as a negative-discovery program. If it succeeds, the success standard has to be very high: not a prettier tensor identity, not a reduced eigenframe toy model, and not another alignment-flavored criterion, but a mechanism that survives full nonlocal coupling and clearly breaks beyond what Tao-style averaging preserves. Anything short of that is obstruction mapping, not a live route.
