../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-004/selector.md:33:These three maximize diversity without carrying a branch whose first likely failure is merely solution-class incompatibility. Chain 01 is the portfolio anchor because it produces the sharpest negative information if nothing operational survives the Tao screen. Chain 02 preserves the single highest-ceiling route by moving to a global critical-element program rather than another local estimate cleanup. Chain 03 supplies the best middle branch: it is structurally different from both 01 and 02, remains close enough to prior pressure-side context to exploit existing knowledge, and is concrete enough to yield a proposition-scale target or a bounded obstruction memo.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The weakness is that it tries to turn a hard object-definition and theorem-calibration problem into a search-and-score problem too early. In this mission, that is dangerous. If "near-closed Tao circuit" has not already survived the Chain 04 invariance audit, then Step 1 just invents a proxy and the rest of the chain optimizes that proxy. Then Step 5 overclaims in both directions: a small-packet partial mimic is treated as a clean kill of the firewall idea, while small-family failure is treated as informative obstruction. Neither inference is earned by the current design.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:9:So the chain is strong as an adversarial stress test and weak as a decisive mission-settling route. Its most likely honest output is a useful diagnostic memo about why small exact packets fail to mimic Tao's circuit, not a clean negative kill and not a theorem-grade positive obstruction.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:13:### Step 1 - Define a Tao-likeness score that can be optimized
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The step assumes Tao's mechanism can be approximated continuously. That may be false. Some load-bearing features are structural or one-sided, not "partially present." A packet that gets 80 percent of a score may still miss the one feature that actually matters.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:29:- Restricting the family up front is good protection against p-hacking. But the chosen minimal families may already prejudge failure. Tao's mechanism uses a highly engineered hierarchy of couplings and scales; there is no reason a one-triad or two-triad packet should be the place where a real exact near-circuit, if one exists, first appears.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:58:- Even a clean transient is not enough. Tao's mechanism is not just any temporary transfer; it is a disciplined delayed-abrupt-transfer architecture with the right hierarchy and with spectators staying subordinate long enough to matter.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- A single small exact packet that "honestly approximates Tao's logic" is not automatically a clean negative kill of the firewall idea. At most it shows that one obstruction formulation is false for one packet class, unless the near-circuit notion has already been fixed robustly and the candidate survives that exact definition.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:67:- The chain silently jumps from "local mimic exists" to "firewall idea should be downgraded immediately." That inference is too strong. Tao's architecture is scale-inductive and hierarchy-sensitive. A local imitation does not yet show the broader exact-NS obstruction is wrong.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:78:Chain 03 is supposed to coexist with Chain 04, but in practice it tries to bypass it. If the stable definition of "near-closed Tao circuit" is not already fixed, then "Tao-likeness" becomes whatever this chain's score function says it is. That makes the search output hard to trust and hard to compare with the other chains.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The mission asks about an exact no-near-closed-Tao-circuit statement. A tiny packet that partially mimics pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic does not by itself refute the broader obstruction. It may only show that one naive formulation was too strict.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:98:The chain is framed as "the fastest way to falsify the firewall idea," and the downstream logic reflects that. A candidate only has to look fairly Tao-like to threaten the obstruction, but the obstruction side is allowed to survive bounded search failure and call it an atlas. That is not symmetric evidence accounting.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:126:The most likely earned output is therefore a bounded memo of the form: among small exact packets, these are the recurring reasons Tao-like delayed transfer fails under honest exact bookkeeping. That is useful. It is just much weaker than what the chain currently promises.
