../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:33:The core objection is correct: geometry and helicity choices determine the ledger itself, so they cannot be postponed until after a lower-bound worksheet is built. Those adversarial degrees of freedom must be present when the packet class and observable are fixed. But the attacker goes too far in implying that collapse on a special family always means the theorem object is wrong. A lower bound on an explicit restricted class can still be mathematically real and mission-useful if its scope is stated honestly.
../../../exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:54:4. It allows three honest endings: a restricted-class positive lower bound, an explicit low-leakage family that preserves Tao-role logic over a stated window, or a precise obstruction showing why leakage-based arguments do not yield a presentable theorem.
