../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:1:# Final Decision Memo - beyond-de-giorgi / run-007
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:7:- from Chain 01: an explicit Tao-discriminator calibration with one passing and one failing example, plus stricter typed failure labels;
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:18:- **useful failure mode:** if it fails, it fails in a way that should produce a clean statement about non-coercivity, mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity escape, localization collapse, or prior-art collapse;
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:19:- **novelty ceiling:** it still preserves a real upside if one coupled energy-helicity quantity survives all gates and reaches a theorem-facing bottleneck;
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:28:- operational Tao calibration;
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:50:- Tao sensitivity must be calibrated up front with one pass and one fail case.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/final-decider.md:57:If the task is to pick the single chain most worth executing now, the right choice is the **energy-helicity route with an early coercivity gate**, not the broader triage protocol and not the more fragile material-variable route.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The likely honest output is therefore a sharp negative memo: the coupled invariant structure is exact but too non-coercive, too prior-art-adjacent, or too fragile under mixed-helicity restoration and localization to move a real continuation or blowup bottleneck.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:15:- The chain lets the user choose among several endpoints, but those endpoints demand very different kinds of leverage. A no-bad-cascade statement, an enstrophy-depletion estimate, and a contradiction on concentrated helicity-bearing regions are not interchangeable faces of one mechanism. Freezing one early risks selecting the endpoint that flatters the invariant package rather than the one the package can honestly touch.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- Banning pure energy reformulations and pure same-helicity folklore is necessary, but it does not solve the deeper problem that helicity may still enter only decoratively. A chain can avoid literal energy-only language while still deriving nothing stronger than energy control plus polarized bookkeeping.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- The hidden assumption is that energy-helicity coupling contains an additional one-sided quantity that can face a regularity endpoint. But helicity density is sign-indefinite, and global helicity mixes scale and chirality rather than directly controlling the bad local term. That assumption should be tested before the endpoint is frozen, not after.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:21:Failure mode: Step 1 locks in an attractive endpoint and ledger before establishing that helicity contributes anything beyond descriptive cascade language.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:23:### Step 2 - Build the exact coupled-flux identity and Tao comparator
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- Writing the energy and helicity transfer identities is easy relative to the real problem. The hard question is whether any coupled identity yields a one-sided estimate after all admissible signs and localizations are restored. The chain risks mistaking "I have an exact balance law" for "I have isolated a usable mechanism."
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:28:- The Tao comparator is underspecified. What exact feature is the averaged model supposed to destroy: phase-sensitive triad geometry, sign-polarized transport, or a nontrivial coupling between scales and chirality? If that feature is not formalized before the comparison, "Tao-sensitive" will be backfilled from whatever survives the chosen decomposition.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:29:- A joint flux can collapse to energy-only control very quickly. The moment one takes absolute values, averages over mixed signs, or uses a generic inequality to compare helicity to energy and enstrophy, the purported extra structure often disappears. The step mentions this risk, but not harshly enough.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- There is a serious decomposition-dependence problem. In helical or dyadic form, one can often make the joint energy-helicity picture look more informative than it is. If the only Tao-sensitive content is a sign-sensitive triad ledger, then the chain has drifted back into the old folklore it claims to transcend.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:39:- "Near-coherent helicity sign" is already suspicious. Coherent sign is close to the same aligned or polarized regimes that prior helical-decimation literature makes look favorable. Unless the chain proves that such coherence captures a quantitatively non-negligible part of the full bad transfer, it has not escaped thin-regime folklore.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:40:- A "forbidden simultaneous transfer pattern" sounds attractive, but it can easily reduce to a triad-sign statement that says certain idealized polarized interactions cannot move energy and helicity in the same way. Full Navier-Stokes does not live on those filtered sectors.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:51:- Mixed-helicity interactions are not a perturbation of the good regime. They are the default full-equation environment. If the gain depends on coherent helicity sign or favorable polarization, then mixed-helicity restoration is not one late test among many. It is the central obstacle and should have been front-loaded.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:52:- Low-helicity regions are equally dangerous. A solution can carry large energy transfer or strong stretching through regions where helicity is small or rapidly changing sign. A route that only sees helicity-bearing coherent regions may simply ignore where the bad dynamics moved.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:53:- Localization is especially damaging here. Helicity is sign-indefinite, and local helicity budgets do not inherit the clean positivity that makes local energy machinery useful. Once cutoffs, flux commutators, and endpoint inequalities are inserted, the coupled-flux gain can evaporate immediately.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- Viscosity is not just one more term to restore. The viscous helicity balance does not behave like a clean positive dissipation identity that can be paired with energy to force depletion. So the "joint invariant" picture becomes less informative exactly where one needs a robust inequality.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:57:Failure mode: Step 4 shows that every apparent gain lived in sign-coherent, filtered, or poorly localized sectors, while the actual full equation keeps the dangerous transfer in mixed or low-helicity regions.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- A proposition-scale positive statement would be especially vulnerable to smuggling the whole difficulty into the hypothesis. For example, assuming a sustained coupled-flux imbalance or persistent helicity coherence strong enough to affect continuation may already encode the missing dynamics.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- The "first missing lemma" is likely not a routine gap. It is likely the entire hard problem: proving that any favorable energy-helicity geometry persists, localizes, and dominates the bad full-equation interactions.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- The negative menu is sensible but too clean. The route may fail for several reasons at once: no one-sided quantity, prior-art collapse, mixed-helicity restoration, and localization failure. Forcing a single typed obstruction can underreport how overdetermined the failure really is.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- The final kill condition is good. If the output still reads as "helicity is interesting," the chain has failed. But the chain should also reject any final claim that reads as "if the solution stays in a strongly polarized helicity regime, then maybe things improve," because that is usually just a dressed-up restatement of the favorable regime.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:78:"Transports both energy and helicity" and "joint transfer geometry" are true, but theorem relevance does not follow from that. Many cascade descriptions are exact and mathematically elegant while remaining useless for continuation or singularity exclusion.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:80:### 3. The Tao screen is too easy to backfill
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The chain says it wants something stronger than energy-only rewrites and older helical folklore, but it does not define the exact Tao-sensitive feature tightly enough. That creates a high risk that the comparator becomes a rhetoric tool rather than a research filter.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:86:Most of the chain's genuine discipline is negative: do not confuse decompositions, do not stop at same-helicity folklore, do not ignore restoration debt. That makes it a credible obstruction program. It does not make it a credible proof route.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:90:The route lives next to helical triad analysis, decimated models, Waleffe-type interaction lore, and familiar statements that favorable helicity polarization depletes transfer in restricted sectors. Without an early novelty threshold, the chain can spend a lot of effort rediscovering that the favorable regime looks favorable.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:94:The premise already suggests that "the true 3D nonlinearity transports both energy and helicity" should hide a deeper invariant geometry. That is plausible as a heuristic, but it also biases the chain toward believing the coupling must mean more than it may actually mean. A fairer design would treat "exact but non-coercive" as the default hypothesis, not the backup hypothesis.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:98:- The chain is right to insist that pure energy-flux rewrites and same-helicity folklore are not enough.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:99:- Step 4 at least names the real debts: mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, viscosity, and localization.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:101:- The final anti-handwaving standard is good: if the end product is merely "helicity matters," the branch has failed.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:105:This is a respectable negative-audit chain and a weak positive chain. Its best contribution is to force a serious answer to a useful question: does exact energy-helicity coupling ever yield a one-sided, localization-stable gain on a named Navier-Stokes bottleneck, or does it collapse into sign-sensitive but non-coercive cascade bookkeeping? My expectation is that the latter is the honest answer.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:107:So the chain is worth running only if it is understood as a short route to a calibrated no-go. If it tries to become a proof program before exhibiting a precise coercive quantity that survives mixed-helicity restoration and localization, it will mostly manufacture elegant invariant rhetoric around a structurally weak idea.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-009-exploration-001-endpoint-menu-freeze.md:181:  observables, or Tao branding before freezing the contradiction line.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-009-exploration-001-endpoint-menu-freeze.md:184:  live, and generic harmonic estimates fail the Tao gate for this branch.
