../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The selected chain has a sound core idea: use Tao's averaged-model obstruction as a filter, refuse fake proof plans, and allow a worthwhile negative outcome. But in its current form it still relies too heavily on soft comparators. It can produce a polished shortlist or obstruction memo without forcing a common theorem-level test early enough.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-01.md:7:The right repair is to keep the branch, but narrow its claims and harden its evidence rules. In particular, the refined chain should force one explicit Tao discriminator, one common comparison frame, earlier compatibility checks, and at least one hard prototype insertion or failed model lemma before any ranking language is trusted.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-01.md:11:### 1. The Tao filter is not yet operational enough to serve as the master selector
