../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:44:### Step 4 - Stress-test Tao sensitivity and packaging robustness
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:49:- The Tao test is still slippery. An averaged quadratic model may destroy a feature for trivial bookkeeping reasons or preserve a feature in a way that says nothing about coercive usefulness. "Not preserved by averaging" is not yet evidence of theorem relevance.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:80:### 4. Tao sensitivity is being asked to do too much conceptual work
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:82:The mission is right to require Tao sensitivity. But "destroyed by averaging" is only a necessary discriminator, not a positive mechanism. A quantity can be genuinely NS-specific and still be analytically powerless. The chain sometimes sounds as if Tao sensitivity itself is a form of leverage.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:86:The negative branch is realistic: one can imagine a sharp memo showing that tensor-pressure structure remains informative yet non-coercive after full nonlocal accounting. The positive branch requires a rare event: a robust, invariant, Tao-sensitive observable that survives harmonic freedom and actually buys a theorem-level gain. The chain does not calibrate those odds honestly enough.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-003.md:11:That means `replan` would be premature. The mission has already paid the replanning cost and has a concrete replacement chain with an ordered first step, explicit Tao-screen discipline, and a bounded success floor. There is no new adverse evidence against this branch yet.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-003.md:19:Its first logical move is still the right next mission action: benchmark candidate geometry mechanisms against prior art, separate genuinely NS-specific ingredients from generic static singular-integral geometry, and operationalize the Tao discriminator before any observable-design work begins.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-003.md:27:- state explicitly what Tao-style averaged models preserve and destroy for each bucket;
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-003.md:30:If that benchmark collapses every candidate to prior-art or Tao-robust static geometry, the branch can be invalidated at the next evaluator pass. Until then, the correct controller action is to proceed.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly right. The original chain has a real research instinct: it tries to test whether full 3D energy-helicity transport contains theorem-relevant structure that is not visible in energy-only or same-helicity-only viewpoints. That is a legitimate target. But the attack correctly identifies the main danger: the chain treats joint energy-helicity flux as if it were already near a coercive mechanism, when in practice helicity is sign-indefinite, cancellation-prone, and hard to localize.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:19:This is a strong criticism. Exact coupled identities are cheap compared with the real burden, which is to show that some coupled quantity survives sign restoration, localization, and ordinary inequality losses without collapsing back to energy-only control. The attack is also correct that the Tao comparator was too underspecified and too easy to backfill from a favorable decomposition.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:24:The attack is correct that this is the decisive step and the original chain did not operationalize the threshold sharply enough. A promoted mechanism must do more than narrate favorable polarized sectors. It must identify how a joint energy-helicity feature reduces one named bad term or excludes one named bad transfer pattern in a quantitatively relevant portion of the full nonlinear burden.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:29:The attack is right that mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, and localization are not late restoration costs. They are architecture-defining constraints for this branch. The original chain named these debts, which is good, but treated them too much as downstream reconstruction rather than as early viability screens.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:39:This is the core issue. Pairing energy with helicity does not itself create a one-sided quantity, and the refined chain must force that question immediately.
