../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-002.md:9:The active chain should not proceed. Step `step-001` was explicitly designed to front-load the Tao gate and kill the branch quickly if no NS-specific coefficient-shrinking mechanism survived the exact far-field reconstruction. That is what happened.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/controller/decisions/decision-002.md:11:This is a branch-level negative result, not a mission-level terminal result. The step pinned down the live far-field pairing, showed that constants were already removed while affine-and-higher harmonic content still survives, and concluded that the remaining obstruction is coefficient-side. Under that reconstruction, the tested harmonic-tail gains are either cosmetic or Tao-compatible.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is disciplined about one real danger: accidentally reviving the dead De Giorgi machinery under Lorentz-space language. That is its best feature. Its main weakness is deeper: weak-type or Lorentz structure is a norm package, not an evident Navier-Stokes-specific mechanism. Under the mission's own Tao filter, that is a serious problem from the start, because weak-type Calderon-Zygmund, interpolation, and endpoint singular-integral technology are exactly the sort of harmonic-analysis assets the averaged model is meant to preserve.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- The proposed package is dominated by generic harmonic-analysis tools: weak-type Calderon-Zygmund bounds, Lorentz interpolation, endpoint pressure estimates. Under the mission context, that is already presumptively Tao-compatible, not a live source of NS-specific leverage.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:33:Failure mode: Step 2 assembles a respectable ledger of weak-type tools that is either Tao-compatible generic analysis or too brittle to survive the local weak-solution setting.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:47:### Step 4 - Charge localization debt and apply the Tao screen
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:51:- The Tao screen should have bitten in Step 2, not after a candidate mechanism is promoted. If the tool package is already weak-type singular integrals plus interpolation, then the branch is already living inside the generic harmonic-analysis zone unless an exact NS-only feature has been named.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:53:- The `4/3` ceiling is not the only relevant failure signature. A route can avoid reproducing the explicit old ceiling and still be dead because it never leaves Tao-compatible analysis or never closes under localization.
../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- The negative-output menu is too narrow for the likely reality. The branch may fail simultaneously because there is no distinct weak-type package, no non-iterative mechanism, and no Tao-sensitive leverage. Forcing a single narrow negative can over-clean the actual obstruction.
