planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:9:The Tao-comparator framing is also weaker than it looks. Showing that Tao's averaged model destroys an exact trajectory-level law is not enough. Many exact structures fail to survive averaging and still have no coercive value for the real equation. The chain quietly assumes that "distinguishes NS from Tao" is evidence of analytical leverage. That implication is not established.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:23:### Step 2 - Write the exact material evolution and the Tao comparator
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:29:The Tao-comparator requirement is also soft in the wrong way. The chain says to identify a feature the averaged model should destroy: exact composition, determinant-one constraints, label alignment, and so on. But which of these features is supposed to matter quantitatively? Many exact Lagrangian identities are algebraically special and analytically useless. Unless the broken Tao feature sits inside the actual endpoint-facing inequality from Step 3, it is just a narrative distinction.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:31:This step also misses prior-art risk. Exact Cauchy-formula-type stretching, deformation gradients, and Lagrangian criteria are already classical terrain. Without an explicit check against known Lagrangian reformulations of BKM and related continuation criteria, the chain may "discover" a Tao-sensitive structure that experts already know does not improve coercivity.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:72:The obstruction menu is also slightly too neat. "Viscous defect dominates," "solution-class mismatch," "nonlocal strain remains free," and "transport structure is exact but analytically non-coercive" are useful failure labels, but actual failure may be broader: the observable may be well-defined only in a regime where the endpoint is already known, or its exact law may exist only in a formulation that destroys the claimed Tao comparison. The chain risks compressing a diffuse failure into a crisp label and thereby overstating what was learned.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:80:The central premise suggests that exact NS transport/stretching laws may only become usable in material variables. That is already a substantive bet, not a neutral starting point. The chain never seriously entertains the stronger contrary hypothesis: exact material structure may be real but analytically inert once viscosity and nonlocality are included. Because of that bias, the plan tends to treat any exact Lagrangian identity as potential leverage instead of demanding evidence that it improves coercivity.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:82:### 2. It overweights distinction from Tao's averaged model
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:84:A route can differ sharply from Tao's averaged model and still be useless for regularity. The relevant question is not "does Tao destroy this exact law?" but "does this exact law force quantitative control that the averaged model cannot fake?" The chain does not make that stronger demand. As written, it may mistake non-robust algebraic structure for analytical leverage.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-02.md:126:So the fair attack is: this chain probably does not fail because one missing lemma remains. It more likely fails because material exactness in 3D Navier-Stokes is not the same thing as material coercivity, and the plan is still too willing to treat the former as evidence for the latter.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The likely honest output is therefore a sharp negative memo: the coupled invariant structure is exact but too non-coercive, too prior-art-adjacent, or too fragile under mixed-helicity restoration and localization to move a real continuation or blowup bottleneck.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:15:- The chain lets the user choose among several endpoints, but those endpoints demand very different kinds of leverage. A no-bad-cascade statement, an enstrophy-depletion estimate, and a contradiction on concentrated helicity-bearing regions are not interchangeable faces of one mechanism. Freezing one early risks selecting the endpoint that flatters the invariant package rather than the one the package can honestly touch.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- Banning pure energy reformulations and pure same-helicity folklore is necessary, but it does not solve the deeper problem that helicity may still enter only decoratively. A chain can avoid literal energy-only language while still deriving nothing stronger than energy control plus polarized bookkeeping.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- The hidden assumption is that energy-helicity coupling contains an additional one-sided quantity that can face a regularity endpoint. But helicity density is sign-indefinite, and global helicity mixes scale and chirality rather than directly controlling the bad local term. That assumption should be tested before the endpoint is frozen, not after.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The minimum quantitative gain is underdefined. "Would change the endpoint" is too soft. The step should demand an explicit reduction of one named bad term or one explicit exclusion pattern. Without that, Step 1 can manufacture a polished setup memo around an invariant that has no coercive meaning.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:21:Failure mode: Step 1 locks in an attractive endpoint and ledger before establishing that helicity contributes anything beyond descriptive cascade language.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:23:### Step 2 - Build the exact coupled-flux identity and Tao comparator
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- Writing the energy and helicity transfer identities is easy relative to the real problem. The hard question is whether any coupled identity yields a one-sided estimate after all admissible signs and localizations are restored. The chain risks mistaking "I have an exact balance law" for "I have isolated a usable mechanism."
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:28:- The Tao comparator is underspecified. What exact feature is the averaged model supposed to destroy: phase-sensitive triad geometry, sign-polarized transport, or a nontrivial coupling between scales and chirality? If that feature is not formalized before the comparison, "Tao-sensitive" will be backfilled from whatever survives the chosen decomposition.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:29:- A joint flux can collapse to energy-only control very quickly. The moment one takes absolute values, averages over mixed signs, or uses a generic inequality to compare helicity to energy and enstrophy, the purported extra structure often disappears. The step mentions this risk, but not harshly enough.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- There is a serious decomposition-dependence problem. In helical or dyadic form, one can often make the joint energy-helicity picture look more informative than it is. If the only Tao-sensitive content is a sign-sensitive triad ledger, then the chain has drifted back into the old folklore it claims to transcend.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:33:Failure mode: Step 2 exports a clean "coupled-flux memo" whose distinguishing feature is either decomposition-specific or non-coercive once signs, absolute values, and localization are paid honestly.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:39:- "Near-coherent helicity sign" is already suspicious. Coherent sign is close to the same aligned or polarized regimes that prior helical-decimation literature makes look favorable. Unless the chain proves that such coherence captures a quantitatively non-negligible part of the full bad transfer, it has not escaped thin-regime folklore.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:40:- A "forbidden simultaneous transfer pattern" sounds attractive, but it can easily reduce to a triad-sign statement that says certain idealized polarized interactions cannot move energy and helicity in the same way. Full Navier-Stokes does not live on those filtered sectors.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:42:- The prior-art benchmark is correctly requested and still too late. Before promoting any mechanism, the chain should force an explicit statement of what is new relative to Waleffe-type analysis, helical shell-model intuition, and decimated same-sign sectors. Otherwise Step 3 will rediscover known favorable subregimes and mistake them for fresh structural leverage.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:45:Failure mode: Step 3 promotes a mechanism that is either a refined story about polarized triads or a cascade slogan with no explicit bridge to the actual bad term.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:51:- Mixed-helicity interactions are not a perturbation of the good regime. They are the default full-equation environment. If the gain depends on coherent helicity sign or favorable polarization, then mixed-helicity restoration is not one late test among many. It is the central obstacle and should have been front-loaded.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:52:- Low-helicity regions are equally dangerous. A solution can carry large energy transfer or strong stretching through regions where helicity is small or rapidly changing sign. A route that only sees helicity-bearing coherent regions may simply ignore where the bad dynamics moved.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:53:- Localization is especially damaging here. Helicity is sign-indefinite, and local helicity budgets do not inherit the clean positivity that makes local energy machinery useful. Once cutoffs, flux commutators, and endpoint inequalities are inserted, the coupled-flux gain can evaporate immediately.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- Viscosity is not just one more term to restore. The viscous helicity balance does not behave like a clean positive dissipation identity that can be paired with energy to force depletion. So the "joint invariant" picture becomes less informative exactly where one needs a robust inequality.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:55:- The classification between "real leverage," "partial leverage," and "non-coercive structure" is good discipline, but by Step 4 the damage may already be done. If the earlier steps never required an explicit map from coupled flux to the actual bad term, the reconstruction ledger will mostly record predictable collapse.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:57:Failure mode: Step 4 shows that every apparent gain lived in sign-coherent, filtered, or poorly localized sectors, while the actual full equation keeps the dangerous transfer in mixed or low-helicity regions.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- A proposition-scale positive statement would be especially vulnerable to smuggling the whole difficulty into the hypothesis. For example, assuming a sustained coupled-flux imbalance or persistent helicity coherence strong enough to affect continuation may already encode the missing dynamics.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- The "first missing lemma" is likely not a routine gap. It is likely the entire hard problem: proving that any favorable energy-helicity geometry persists, localizes, and dominates the bad full-equation interactions.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:65:- The negative menu is sensible but too clean. The route may fail for several reasons at once: no one-sided quantity, prior-art collapse, mixed-helicity restoration, and localization failure. Forcing a single typed obstruction can underreport how overdetermined the failure really is.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- The final kill condition is good. If the output still reads as "helicity is interesting," the chain has failed. But the chain should also reject any final claim that reads as "if the solution stays in a strongly polarized helicity regime, then maybe things improve," because that is usually just a dressed-up restatement of the favorable regime.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:72:### 1. The chain treats a sign-indefinite invariant as if it might become coercive by pairing it with energy
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:78:"Transports both energy and helicity" and "joint transfer geometry" are true, but theorem relevance does not follow from that. Many cascade descriptions are exact and mathematically elegant while remaining useless for continuation or singularity exclusion.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:80:### 3. The Tao screen is too easy to backfill
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The chain says it wants something stronger than energy-only rewrites and older helical folklore, but it does not define the exact Tao-sensitive feature tightly enough. That creates a high risk that the comparator becomes a rhetoric tool rather than a research filter.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:86:Most of the chain's genuine discipline is negative: do not confuse decompositions, do not stop at same-helicity folklore, do not ignore restoration debt. That makes it a credible obstruction program. It does not make it a credible proof route.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:90:The route lives next to helical triad analysis, decimated models, Waleffe-type interaction lore, and familiar statements that favorable helicity polarization depletes transfer in restricted sectors. Without an early novelty threshold, the chain can spend a lot of effort rediscovering that the favorable regime looks favorable.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:94:The premise already suggests that "the true 3D nonlinearity transports both energy and helicity" should hide a deeper invariant geometry. That is plausible as a heuristic, but it also biases the chain toward believing the coupling must mean more than it may actually mean. A fairer design would treat "exact but non-coercive" as the default hypothesis, not the backup hypothesis.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:98:- The chain is right to insist that pure energy-flux rewrites and same-helicity folklore are not enough.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:99:- Step 4 at least names the real debts: mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, viscosity, and localization.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:101:- The final anti-handwaving standard is good: if the end product is merely "helicity matters," the branch has failed.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:105:This is a respectable negative-audit chain and a weak positive chain. Its best contribution is to force a serious answer to a useful question: does exact energy-helicity coupling ever yield a one-sided, localization-stable gain on a named Navier-Stokes bottleneck, or does it collapse into sign-sensitive but non-coercive cascade bookkeeping? My expectation is that the latter is the honest answer.
planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:107:So the chain is worth running only if it is understood as a short route to a calibrated no-go. If it tries to become a proof program before exhibiting a precise coercive quantity that survives mixed-helicity restoration and localization, it will mostly manufacture elegant invariant rhetoric around a structurally weak idea.
