 # Strategizer Reasoning
 
 The strategizer will append its execution reasoning here.
+
+## Iteration 1 - Startup, receptionist packet, and exploration freeze
+
+- Read `GOAL.md`, `state.json`, `HISTORY-OF-REPORT-SUMMARIES.md`,
+  `CHAIN.md`, and the run-007 section of `CHAIN-HISTORY.md`.
+- Queried the receptionist through `bin/run-role.sh` before planning
+  explorations, as required.
+- Read receptionist result
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T182129Z-receptionist-83682.md`.
+- Strongest receptionist findings adopted:
+  - the best-supported burden family is `stretching/enstrophy bottleneck`;
+  - the sharpest invariant package on the local record is `dyadic coupled
+    fluxes`;
+  - the current repository does not already contain a standalone exact
+    energy/helicity identity sheet for this branch;
+  - the best Tao screen packet is the canonicalization screen plus the exact-NS
+    helical packet/firewall reports;
+  - the branch is already under explicit warnings of
+    `exact but non-coercive` / `prior-art-adjacent` collapse unless Step 1 can
+    name a one-sided gain on a theorem-facing bad term.
+- Execution decision after the receptionist:
+  - run three bounded explorations, because the step still needs source-backed
+    artifacts even though the likely verdict is negative;
+  - `exploration-001` freezes the scope lock and tests whether the baseline and
+    gain threshold can be made concrete enough to avoid immediate setup
+    obstruction;
+  - `exploration-002` writes the exact dyadic coupled-flux ledger as far as the
+    repository permits and operationalizes the Tao screen with one pass and one
+    fail case;
+  - `exploration-003` screens prior-art collapse and writes the final Step-1
+    verdict recommendation.
+
